INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES (1,1,1,'Great for solo studying, and an occasional nap',4.0,NULL,'H2O Stations, Late Hours, Quiet, Bike Parking','2025-04-13 20:45:03'),(2,1,2,'Great for quiet group study, not ideal for eating or talking',3.0,NULL,'H2O Stations, Late Hours, Quiet, Bike Parking','2025-04-13 20:45:12'),(3,1,3,'Great food, fills up fast and limited room for groups larger than 2 people',5.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, Indie (Non-Chain), Vegans Welcome','2025-04-13 20:45:25'),(4,1,7,'Small space, limited outlets',2.0,NULL,'Bike Parking, Pet Friendly','2025-04-13 20:46:06'),(5,1,8,'Small space, limited outlets',2.0,NULL,'Bike Parking, Pet Friendly','2025-04-13 20:46:14'),(6,1,10,'Vegan food, lots of space, some outlets, usually a little loud',4.0,NULL,'Vegans Welcome, Aesthetic, Indie (Non-Chain)','2025-04-13 20:46:36'),(7,1,11,'Relaxed study spot, not a lot of tables at arm level so not great for long laptop sessions',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, H2O Stations, BYOF','2025-04-13 20:46:48'),(8,1,13,'You can reserve rooms here, which makes it ideal for a weekly group meetings, or anything regular since you can guarantee a spot with outlets and whiteboard walls at a specific time/date. Also great for solo studying',5.0,NULL,'H2O Stations, BYOF, Quiet','2025-04-13 20:47:13'),(9,1,14,'Super crowded but a lot of places to get food and a decent number of outlets, but you have to really search for them. Certain hours, like lunch and dinner are bad times to go in to study but it\'s good if you want to eat and then stay late. Also a great spot for early morning studying',4.0,NULL,'H2O Stations, Late Hours, Early Hours, BYOF','2025-04-13 20:47:24'),(10,1,15,'Limited seating to work, practically no outlets',2.0,NULL,'Bike Parking, BYOF','2025-04-13 20:47:35'),(11,1,16,'Loud and busy but they don\'t mind if you spend several hours taking up a bar space',3.0,NULL,'Smiley Service','2025-04-13 20:47:46'),(12,1,17,'Loud and busy but they don\'t mind if you spend several hours taking up a bar space',3.0,NULL,'Early Hours, Smiley Service','2025-04-13 20:47:58'),(13,1,18,'Smaller space, limited outlets and limited space for groups bigger than 2 people',3.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, Indie (Non-Chain), Vegans Welcome','2025-04-13 20:48:09'),(14,1,19,'Smaller space, limited outlets and limited space for groups bigger than 2 people',3.0,NULL,'Early Hours, Smiley Service','2025-04-13 20:48:20'),(15,1,20,'Small space, limited outlets',2.0,NULL,'Bike Parking, Pet Friendly','2025-04-13 20:48:31'),(16,1,21,'Larger spot than Starbucks, pretty good food and plenty of comfy chairs. Outlets might be a little difficult to find. They also have outdoor seating in good weather',3.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, Indie (Non-Chain)','2025-04-13 20:48:43'),(17,1,25,'Bottom floor is very quiet and ideal for long study sessions',5.0,NULL,'Low-Traffic, Low-Light, Early Hours','2025-04-13 20:49:29'),(18,1,27,'Lots of little nooks to sit and study, not as many places to meet in large groups. There\'s a 2nd floor study space that fills up fast that has more outlets and seats',5.0,NULL,'Quiet, BYOF','2025-04-13 20:49:50'),(19,2,1,'Great place to feel motivated because there\'s always a bunch of students studying here. A good spot for group studying because it isn\'t quiet so you don\'t have to worry about others. There\'s a variety of spots so you can find what you need. It\'s convenient that it\'s near the city market too. The lights are always on and bright so even at night, it feels like it\'s earlier. I only wish the chairs were comfier and the furniture was more up-to-date. It can be kind of drab sometimes. There are also isn\'t water fountain on each floor. Restrooms alternate with female and male which can be super annoying.',4.0,NULL,'Early Hours, H2O Stations, Late Hours','2025-04-16 18:25:03'),(20,2,2,'Perfect for really grinding because it\'s super quiet. Very convenient that it\'s near the city market. Restrooms alternate with female and male which can be super annoying. Wish the chairs were comfier. Kinda feels like a jail cell sometimes especially there are literal boarded rooms.',2.5,NULL,'Early Hours, Late Hours, Quiet','2025-04-16 18:25:14'),(21,2,3,'Atmosphere is great, really gives that aesthetic coffee shop feel. Good for collaborating and has comfy chairs. Can be busy quickly tho so sometimes hard to find good seats. Actual coffee isn\'t great tho and overpriced. For some reason, the different flavors all taste the same and are never sweet enough. Food\'s good but also overpriced.',3.5,NULL,'Aesthetic, Indie (Non-Chain), Early Hours','2025-04-16 18:25:26'),(22,2,4,'Very aesthetic, feels like you\'re in an Apple store. Absolutely hate how the seats are not functional tho, literally just asking to give everyone back pain. The seats near Saxby\'s have good back support but no outlets :( Love Saxby\'s coffee too especially the vanilla bean latte and the matcha protein drink, just can\'t stand the price! It\'s ridiculous to charge students $7 to $9 for a drink, especially when Saxby\'s prides itself on being student-run! French toast muffin is a real treat and big, really good. But the bacon, chicken, ranch grilled cheese tasted like it was microwaved and didn\'t sit well. I am a fan of the green initiative they are doing tho but the reusable cups don\'t really seem clean ?',3.0,'CDS_121.jpg,CDS_122.jpg,CDS_123.jpg','Aesthetic, Early Hours, Late Hours, H2O Stations, BYOF, Smiley Service','2025-04-16 18:25:37'),(23,2,5,'Love studying in the large study room. Every seat has outlets for 2-pin, usb, AND usb-c which is so rare. And each row is so spacious. Room is great for solo or group studying as the sound is moderate. There are a few round tables that are good for collaboration but the outlets don\'t fit a lot of plugs. The meeting rooms are usually locked but when they are open, it\'s a really good space to work with a team. There are also whiteboards in the meeting rooms and against the back wall. The large windows also give a nice view of BU.',5.0,'CDS_221.jpg,CDS_222.jpg,CDS_223.jpg','Aesthetic, Early Hours, Late Hours, H2O Stations, BYOF','2025-04-16 18:25:49'),(24,2,6,'Really nice view and has outdoor patio. Doesn\'t have many outlets though. Has a microwave which is great to heat up food from home and also has the small Terrier Bytes cafe where you can buy snacks from. Can get packed quick.',4.0,'CDS_321.jpg,CDS_322.jpg,CDS_323.jpg','Aesthetic, Early Hours, Late Hours, BYOF, Quiet','2025-04-16 18:26:01'),(25,2,9,'Very cozy and has a lot of space. Drinks and food are good too. Need to visit more often!',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, Early Hours','2025-04-16 18:26:35'),(26,2,10,'Love this spot for studying all day! Has pillows at most tables and jars of water that you can bring to your table so you can get really comfy here. Also has outlets at most tables! Offers a variety of fresh and healthy vegan food and drinks that is pretty good. I\'ve brought outside food here too and haven\'t had an issue. My favorite part is that they have a room in the back that is super cozy and has a nice ambiance. AND it is a lot quieter than the rest of the cafe so it\'s perfect when you need a change in environment.',5.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, Early Hours, Vegans Welcome, Smiley Service, H2O Stations','2025-04-16 18:26:46'),(27,2,11,'This spot can be a hit or miss depending on the time. It is normally a great space to go to with comfy seating and large windows facing Commonwealth. It also has some games that you can play when you need to take a break. However, being a community center, sometimes they have events or have people meeting up which can be distracting or a bit annoying because people studying could be asked to leave. So try to see if they have any events that day before heading over. I\'m not sure if they have it listed online but you can ask the front desk.',4.0,NULL,'BYOF, H2O Stations','2025-04-16 18:26:58'),(28,2,12,'A new spot in BU, I don\'t think many people really know much about it yet. It\'s a bit hidden and located above the Howard Thurman Center. Since it\'s new, it has nice amenities like the furniture.',5.0,NULL,'Low-Traffic, Quiet','2025-04-16 18:27:09'),(29,2,13,'Has outlets at each desk. Definitely a more modern feel. Great for collaborative or solo studying. And it\'s generally open late too.',5.0,NULL,'Quiet','2025-04-16 18:27:21'),(30,2,14,'Honestly a bit too distracting for my taste, it\'s always crowded and loud but has easy access to food. Not sure if there are a lot of convenient outlets too. There\'s a microwave so you can bring your own food too but it\'s not clean a lot of times and smells weird.',3.5,NULL,'Early Hours, Late Hours, BYOF, H2O Stations','2025-04-16 18:27:32'),(31,2,15,'Good if you wanted to get something quick done before/after working out. Not sure if I would really study here otherwise. It\'s definitely loud and not a lot of spaces. High tables too without outlets.',3.0,NULL,'Early Hours, Late Hours, BYOF, H2O Stations','2025-04-16 18:27:44'),(32,2,16,'This is a good spot if it\'s not busy. You can post up in your own booth and you\'ll have a lot of space to yourself and there are outlets at each booth! Food is so good too. And they\'ll give you your own pitcher of water too. But if they get busy, they will ask you to give up your table so keep that in mind. And on weekends, they are so busy that you need a reservation or you\'ll have a crazy wait time so I wouldn\'t recommend studying here on the weekends. I think weekday mornings are the best time. It can get loud when it\'s busy too.',3.5,NULL,'Aesthetic, Late Hours, H2O Stations','2025-04-16 18:27:55'),(33,2,17,'Can get really busy so it can be hard to find a spot sometimes. But I like the cafe atmosphere it gives. Especially the seating outside is a nice change of scenery. The spots against the wall has outlets and faces the lively St. Mary\'s Street. There is a big table too which is good for collaborative work. Food and drinks are really yummy too. My favorite is their seasonal ginger date latte, sooo good.',4.5,NULL,'Early Hours, Aesthetic','2025-04-16 18:28:06'),(34,2,19,'Bigger than the one on St. Mary\'s. Can get really busy so it can be hard to find a spot sometimes. But I like the cafe atmosphere it gives. Food and drinks are really yummy too. My favorite is their seasonal ginger date latte, sooo good.',5.0,NULL,'Early Hours','2025-04-16 18:28:29'),(35,2,21,'Very cozy and is massive. There\'s usually spots open and the seats are very comfy. Drinks and food are good too. Need to visit more often!',5.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, Early Hours','2025-04-16 18:28:52'),(36,2,22,'Food and drinks are AMAZING. I love the sea salt vietnamese coffee. I wish the space was bigger because it can get very crowded and is hard to get a seat sometimes. There is this really cute secluded spot in the corner that has a desk and two chairs and cute decor that is nice for studying. Can get loud as well but workers are really friendly and generally a good atmosphere.',4.5,NULL,'Aesthetic, Early Hours, Smiley Service, Indie (Non-Chain)','2025-04-16 18:29:03'),(37,2,23,'Pretty strict about outside food but also doesn\'t offer food which is annoying. Drinks are decent but pretty unique. There isn\'t a lot of seating and the outlets aren\'t super convenient. I would say go here if you only need to study for a few hours.',2.5,NULL,'Quiet, Indie (Non-Chain)','2025-04-16 18:29:15'),(38,3,1,'I go here when I need to print something quickly. During finals, they set up little de-stress stations with puzzles or coloring — a nice touch!',4.5,NULL,'Quiet, Late Hours','2025-04-15 01:57:03'),(39,3,3,'A fun place to chill or work solo. I just wish it stayed open a bit later because the vibe is so good.',3.5,NULL,'Aesthetic, Indie (Non-Chain)','2025-04-15 01:57:26'),(40,3,14,'I usually go here around prayer time since there\'s a prayer room on the second floor. It’s also a good spot to work on assignments , tables for group work and comfy couches make it feel welcoming.',5.0,NULL,'Meetings, Quiet','2025-04-15 01:59:32'),(41,3,17,'I love their Tatte latte with cardamom (reminds me of Arabic coffee). Great seating and good ambiance for short study sessions or relaxed work time.',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, Indie (Non-Chain), Late Hours','2025-04-15 02:00:17'),(42,3,26,'This was one of the first places I found to pray on campus. The staff were so kind and the meditation room is quiet and peaceful — perfect for reflection.',4.0,NULL,'Quiet','2025-04-15 02:01:59'),(43,3,27,'I attended a Saudi event here — the hall was elegant with round tables and a big screen. Seems perfect for formal events.',5.0,NULL,'Quiet, Low-Traffic','2025-04-15 02:02:10'),(44,4,1,'Always a solid choice. Genuinely one of the few spots I can rely on after dark. Multiple services: printing, outlets, you name it. Bit too dark for my liking but I’ll keep coming back.',4.0,NULL,'Late hours, quiet, H2O stations, bike parking','2025-04-13 21:48:14'),(45,4,2,'Generally prefer the upper floors if I’m coming with others. Tend to be more crowded in my experience but still one of the only spots that opens as late as they do. So necessary!',4.0,NULL,'Late hours, bike parking, H2O stations','2025-04-13 21:48:27'),(46,4,3,'Would come here so much more often if it weren’t for the crowds. Great coffee, great ambience but I can’t always be guaranteed a spot.',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic','2025-04-13 21:48:39'),(47,4,4,'Such a gorgeous building but so many peopleee. If you’re coming during peak hours, best of luck finding a spot. Saxby’s cafe is pretty decent too.',3.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, courtyard, H2O stations','2025-04-13 21:48:51'),(48,4,5,'I come here often. It’s a good place to park - CDS is scarcely empty so it’s sometimes effort to find a spot. And not a huge number of outlets here but still solid.',3.5,NULL,'Quiet, late hours, H2O stations','2025-04-13 21:49:02'),(49,4,6,'Always frequent this space. It’s usually reliable in terms of nabbing a seat, so bright and never too loud. I’ve got classes just below so it’s probably one of my favourites across campus.',5.0,NULL,'BYOF, quiet, H2O stations, courtyard','2025-04-13 21:49:14'),(50,4,7,'I avoid Starbucks because I loathe the coffee and there’s so many better options on campus that are less sad interior-wise. A plus though because they open real early and later than a lot of other locations too.',2.5,NULL,'Late hours, early hours','2025-04-13 21:49:26'),(51,4,8,'Loathe the coffee and there’s so many better options on campus that are less sad interior-wise. A plus though because they open earlier than any other place I know.',2.5,NULL,'Early hours','2025-04-13 21:49:38'),(52,4,9,'As a Brit, Caffè Nero always brings me back home :) Genuinely good quality coffee and pastries for a chain. They’ve got several outlets and I’ve never found it to be rowdy or difficult to come by one.',5.0,NULL,'Late hours, quiet, smiley service','2025-04-13 21:49:50'),(53,4,10,'Can’t recommend enough IF you’re willing to pay the prices. It’s peaceful and genuinely well decorated. There’s a good number of them across the city and the quality is so consistent. Always feel a bit awkward about overstaying but it’s prime. Not my favourite coffee though.',4.5,NULL,'Late hours, vegans welcome, aesthetic','2025-04-13 21:50:02'),(54,4,11,'Not a HUGE seating capacity, but so bright and quiet. I’m a fan. If I’ve got lessons here, I’m definitely staying over after.',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, quiet, low-traffic','2025-04-13 21:50:14'),(55,4,12,'Love that this space exists. Don\'t know why I haven\'t tried here more times. Not too roomy but a good fallback.',3.0,NULL,'Low-traffic, bike parking','2025-04-13 21:50:26'),(56,4,14,'If you work well this noise this is such a good one. You’ve got all the food options around you but you’re not obligated to buy anything. No one\'s gonna fuss if you bring your own. Bit too loud for me personally but when it gets late it quietens down for sure.',3.5,NULL,'Late hours, BYOF','2025-04-13 21:50:50'),(57,4,15,'Not the most comfortable ever, but if you’re in between gym classes I’d say it’s alright.',2.5,NULL,'BYOF, H2O stations','2025-04-13 21:51:01'),(58,4,16,'Quite dimly lit and not a quiet atmosphere. I’d never come here first, but it’s a good fallback imo. If you want to eat it’s a good option, but if you’re paying anyway then you can find other cafes more apt for studying.',3.0,NULL,'Low-light, late hours','2025-04-13 21:51:13'),(59,4,17,'Tatte’s pretty beautiful inside and they’re definitely not laptop-unfriendly. Feels a bit uncomfortable to stay too long cause they’re definitely very popular. For a shorter study sesh it’s optimal. And the menu has some great items too.',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, late hours','2025-04-13 21:51:24'),(60,4,18,'Would come here so much more often if it weren’t for the crowds. Great coffee, great ambience but I can’t always be guaranteed a spot. This one is busier than other branches though so just bear that in mind.',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic','2025-04-13 21:51:36'),(61,4,19,'Tatte’s pretty beautiful inside and they’re definitely not laptop-unfriendly. Feels a bit uncomfortable to stay too long cause they’re definitely very popular. For a shorter study sesh it’s optimal. This one is busier than other branches though so just bear that in mind.',4.0,NULL,'Aesthetic, late hours','2025-04-13 21:51:47'),(62,4,20,'Loathe the coffee and there’s so many better options on campus that are less sad interior-wise. But literally the most flexible hours around.',3.0,NULL,'Early hours, late hours','2025-04-13 21:51:59'),(63,4,21,'Genuinely good quality coffee and pastries for a chain. They’ve got several outlets and I’ve never found it to be rowdy or difficult to come by one. This one is busier than other branches though so just bear that in mind.',4.5,NULL,'Late hours, quiet, smiley service','2025-04-13 21:52:11'),(64,4,22,'A really lovely spot but I hardly come here to study because it’s just too little and you can\'t be guaranteed space.',3.5,NULL,'Courtyard, smiley service, aesthetic','2025-04-13 21:52:22'),(65,4,23,'A really lovely spot but I hardly come here to study because it’s just too little and you can\'t be guaranteed space.',3.5,NULL,'Smiley service, aesthetic, indie (non-chain)','2025-04-13 21:52:34'),(66,4,24,'Not bad at all. It’s really really little, but again if you’ve got lessons here it’s ideal. And you’ve got Einstein’s a couple floors away. Only thing is they close pretty early.',3.5,NULL,'Quiet, bike parking','2025-04-13 21:52:46'),(67,4,25,'Small-ish and pretty dark. If your in the area it\'s alright but I\'d never travel for it',2.5,NULL,'Low-light, quiet','2025-04-13 21:52:58'),(68,4,27,'If you scour Questrom you can usually find a spot. It\'s not my go-to but it\'s always a good one for in between classes.',3.5,NULL,'Bike parking, low-traffic','2025-04-13 21:53:21');
